2006/04/01:
  * Experimental: SWT supports virtual trees now, so all trees have been made virtual. 
    (downloads tree) They sort & update much faster and alternating tableRow colors are 
    quicker to update (if enabled in prefs->display). 
    (win32 requires XP with manifest for best flicker-free results)
  * Tables: Disabled sort-column colour configuration - SWT now uses the OS's setting
  * Files/clients not reporting chunk availability will have their chunk graphs rendered in
    all black (if chunk graphs are enabled)
  * Sharing strategies added to the share dialog ("+" button in shares tab) [#1427308]
  * Clicking status line when it reports new messages will switch to friends tab [#1431001]
  * Changed Razorback2 web service link
  * Prefs->Downloads->Web services lets you set up a few of your own web services that 
    will be added to the rt-click menu. The URL allows %FILEHASH% %FILESIZE% and %FILEED2K%
    replacement variables.
  * Add preference to disable version popup on new verions (Prefs->general) (#1411070)
    - If "new version check" is enabled, the statusline will still be updated but there 
    will be no popup if this option is disabled
  * Servers: DoubleClick servers to toggle connect/disconnect status
  * Fix: crash on delete keypress in File Details->Subfiles table
  * SWT updates: 
    - chunk graphs should now work on gtk 
    - x86_64 version should load properly
    - OSX blank white box (due to web browser) should be fixed
    - OSX now has a universal binary (for ppc and intel)

