2006/01/02:
  * Add Preview subMenu to shared files -- works by connecting to the web interface 
    preview port (remember to set a preview app in transfers->preview that supports 
    http (ie: vlc))
  * Add File details rt-click menuItem to shared files that have sub files available
  * Add "Download (local)" menuItem to all preview subMenus. This uses the preview 
    function of the mldonkey web interface and saves the bytes to disk (useful 
    if your core is remote).  Set a default download dir in Prefs->Transfers->
    Preview Download directory.  Requires access to the web interface port of 
    mldonkey (or ssh port forward it in the host manager, [gcj bug: gcj compiled 
    binaries don't work when downloading over ssh2 fowarded ports [IOexception]). 
    Download individual files from multiFiles from the FileInfo subfile table.
    (mldonkey seems to send files slower than a normal web server)
    Requires latest mldonkey 
