2004/03/07:
  * Preference pages are not hidden in a tree anymore
  * win32 distribution is now a simple installer with uninstall option
  * Added option to use the core's new internal streaming preview URL
    Prefs->Transfers->Preview
    - You can set a local preview app and if you toggle the streaming option on, 
    the first cmdline param will be the http url of the core's stream of the file
    instead of a local filename (if your preview app supports http streams)
    - The settings for the URL are derived from your current core connection, and 
    the http_port of your core settings
    - tested with mplayer.exe on windows (works)
      - set previewExecutable to "c:\mplayer\mplayer.exe"
      - set previewWorkingDirectory to "c:\mplayer"
    - note: seems to fail if you use a password in mldonkey 
      (mplayer bug? mldonkey bug? it fails even from cmdline)
  * If using the "spawn core from within sancho" option, the gui port is now 
    checked to see if it is already open, and if so, doesn't spawn another 
    core but only connects to the existing one (and kills it when closed)
    
