2004/02/09:
  * Add pending (uploaders) slots table (initially hidden & disabled)
    - doubleClick "uploaders" header to view it ("+" to enable updates)
    - requires latest mldonkey (2.5-11)
  * Uploaders table now shows bittorrent clients (latest mldonkey required)
  * Configurable poll delay: Preferences->sancho->Transfers
    - poll the core every X seconds for uploaders/pending/upstats(shares)
  * Add disconnect/connect rt-clk context menu option to all clients (requires
    latest mldonkey 2.5-11)
  * Fix #893771 (failure to close after ed2k link clicked)
  * Fix row selection on fox
  * Per row fonts now available on gtk and motif (see 02/06)
  * Added ability to configure language file support:
    - sancho.properties is a "key = value" text file.  It can be renamed and
    translated to other languages (in /distrib dir) (ie: sancho_de_DE.properties) 
    - If you make a translation, send it in and it will be included by default
     (email or submit it as a patch)
    - properties files must be in your $HOME/.sancho/ directory, examples:
      c:\documents and settings\username\.sancho\sancho_en_US.properties
      /home/username/.sancho/sancho_fr_FR.properties
    - WINDOWS: You might have to copy this file to the directory containing
        "sancho.exe" (gcj windows compiler bug)
    Once the file is copied there, you can select it and restart sancho:
    - Preferences->sancho->general->locale (lists available files, blank = none)
    - Naming conventions are from the Java Locale class:
    http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.1/docs/api/java/util/Locale.html  

